16 WHEREAS, the framing of this house on the state capitol grounds serves as a powerful
17 reminder of the impact that collaborative efforts can have in creating positive change and
18 fostering stronger, more resilient communities.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
20 commend Habitat for Humanity Georgia and its Georgia affiliates for their unwavering
21 dedication to affordable housing and community advocacy as well as recognize March 5,
22 2025, as Habitat for Humanity Georgia Day at the state capitol.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
24 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
25 press.
